measure.CatchLine: Requires the Department of Land Conservation and Development to study housing development opportunities conditioned upon land conservation.
measure.MeasureSummary:
Digest: This Act makes DLCD study housing credits. (Flesch Readability Score: 66.7). 
	Requires the Department of Land Conservation and Development to study housing development opportunities conditioned upon land conservation. Directs the department to submit findings to the interim committees of the Legislative Assembly related to land use no later than September 15, 2027. 
	Sunsets on January 2, 2028.
measure.RelatingToFull: Relating to housing development opportunities conditioned upon land conservation.
measure.RelatingTo: Relating to housing development opportunities conditioned upon land conservation.
measure.FiscalImpact: May have fiscal impact, but no statement yet issued
measure.RevenueImpact: May have revenue impact, but no statement yet issued

historyActions.ActionText: First reading. Referred to Speaker's desk.
